9. M. Cispius was plebeian tribune in 57 B.c. when Cicero was restored from exile. He exerted himself on Cicero’s behalf, and as a result was maltreated by Clodius’ hired ruffians. He was also aecused by his politieal opponents of ambitus, and, in spite of Cicero’s pathetie defenee of him, was convicted.
